INSERT INTO `tag_essay` VALUES(179, 14, 71, 0, '\nDo you agree or disagree with the following statement? The most important period in a person’s life is one’s twenties. Use specific reasons and examples to support your opinion.', '"Frankly, each person has some golden periods in one’s life time and there are some who believe that the period might be one’s twenties. However, I strongly believe that the most important period is one’s sixties because of plentiful time, money and well organized thoughts.\n\nTo begin with, most of the twenties are too busy with choosing their careers and they are not wealthy enough to enjoy their lives or challenge for something new. For the person who is in the important period should be manifestly supported by money and time so that they can discover and plan their own future. According to the report by the Washington Citizens Foundation, seniors were better in accomplishing the things that they have planned because they had adequate amount of money and time. Also, their satisfactory in their lives were much higher than twenties as well. As the example shows, twenties cannot be the most important period because of money and time to try for something they really long for.\n\nIn addition, the young do not possess any of useful experience which means they are not ready to explore the world with the proper thoughts. On the other hand, seniors obviously have well developed knowledge which is useful and helpful to start their real life that they have wanted for the whole 50years. From my personal experience, my grandfather is a successful old man in his business field nowadays, while he had a big failure in his business when he was 25 years old. He had a hard time for a long time and he made an enterprise at age sixty which is now a successful and well-known company throughout the world. It was an experience that he has accumulated for a long time which brought him a fame and strong company.\n\nIn conclusion, I do strongly believe that twenties are not the most important period in one’s life."', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 'essay', 'Tagging', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
INSERT INTO `tag_essay` VALUES(180, 14, 72, 0, '\n"In today''s society, having much money is more important that gaining public recognition."', '"In today''s society, it is widely believed that gaining public recognition is still more important tat haveing much money. Some people advocate that money can not buy one''s recognition from the society, the recognition that lasts forever. However, I disagree with this view. I firmly believe that making a lot of money is the far more crucial than receiving the respect. This is because first, money can make the reveration and second, money will create more chance to do something very helpful for people in the world.\n\nFirst of all, The finance power, itself is what people believe to be respect. In other words, More money I have, the more venerable things I have done, including studying hard, working hard and being smatter. For example, according to the study done by New York Times, it revealed that People hold that the money one has show the byproducts with which he made significant efforts in life, efforts that are people follow. This study show that the money is the result of rewards of people who have done all things worthy not only for themselves buy also human kind. If so, one with money have also admiration from people. This fact clearly show that earning wealthy is better to do that recognition.\n\nSecond, the money gives us more priceless opportunity benificial for the community. To be specific, The rich paying subtantial tax amount provides healthy support neighbourhood, making themselves abundant. They are also easy to spend much on the variety of commodity, with the result that capital circulates around them. To illustrate, Bill Gates who is one of the richest in the world and who was CEO of microsoft, the biggest computer software company paid uncountable amount of tax for the municipal. The tax was much more than was the case with ordinary people, so that the goverment provide high-quality education for the student who lived near the Mr. Gates. such as a laptop for each and real animals they can study. They were growned up as the people who remember the support they got and, actually, provides another chance to the community. On the other hand, if Bill gates had gotten only recognition as a respectable CEO without financing effect on local, the student would have not been people who offer more help to the area. This strongly refelcts that making money is more important.\n\nAll things considered, it is my belief that my argument regarding this topic effectively and preciesly delivered with the reasons mentioned above. Never should we forget that this will have huge impact for our future."', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 'essay', 'Tagging', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
INSERT INTO `tag_essay` VALUES(181, 14, 73, 0, '\nPeople should try several different jobs before getting a long term job.', '"There is an argument over whether people should try several different job before getting long term job. Some might argue that doing several jobs is better. However, in my view, getting long term job at once is better. There are several reasons that I could support my argument so I will limit my discussion to the two that I feel are the most relevant to the topic. First, people can succeed. Also, people can save time.\n\nTo begin with, the most important reason for my feeling this way is that people can become successful. Generally in society, many accomplished people tend to have expertise. Thus, it can be said that people can become successful because they can get expertise by getting long term job first. A really good example can be seen in Minhan Kim. I read online that Kim, the CEO of CS company achieved great success because he got his job at once. Kim, by using expertise, transformed his company into one of the most profitable software enterprises in Korea. He got his job in software company at once, so he could learn more useful skills than other programmers who entered software company later because of previous jobs. This example clearly shows that it is worse to try different jobs before getting a long term job because of success.\n\nMoreover, another reason which proves my point is that people can save much time. Most often, time is very important in our everyday lives. If people get their long term job at once, they will make the most of their time. Take my uncle, for example. It was really efficiency to get long term job at once. It took only 5 years to become senior manager in his company. In contrast, his friend Tom took 10 years to do same because he had got many different jobs before. Unlike Tom, my uncle did not have to spend time on unnecessary jobs. This result clearly shows that it is better to get long term job at once.\nAll things considered, with the reasons mentioned above, I believe I have sufficiently and adequately explained my position on the matters regarding this topic."', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 'essay', 'Tagging', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
INSERT INTO `tag_essay` VALUES(182, 14, 74, 0, '\nIt is better to have friends who are similar to you than those who are different from you.', '"Some people think that it is better to have friends who are similar to them than those who are different from them. However, in my opinion, different friends are much more helpful because with various friends, people can give and receive diverse opinion in same subject and are helped to adapt to society in the future as well as in the present. \n\nFirstly, friends who grew in the varied environment have definitely different opinion even in the same subject. When people communicate with them, they can broaden their view of the world and improve abilities of understanding other people. For example, in the High School, I have friends whom other classmates called them strange. In this time, I could really get and build broad mind because they make me like that. \n\nOn top of that, different friends help people to be able to adapt to society in the present and even in the  future. They are different in ways to meet and manage varying situations. When people watch them and are affected by the ways they receive the situations, they can develop their own way which they couldn’t take alone. For instance, after graduating High School when I grew with the friend I mentioned above, I really adapted well to University even if there are a lot of unkind and ungenerous people. I think it is due to my high-school friends’ lives. \n\nTo sum up, in the environment with different types of friends, people broaden their opinion of the world and can develop ability to live in the society without the bigger problem. In this regard, I disagree with the statement that it is better to have friends who are lots of afimities than those who are different."', 'Some people think that it is better to have friends who are similar to them than those who are different from them. However, in my opinion, different friends are much more helpful because with various friends, people can give and receive diverse opinion in same subject and are helped to adapt to society in the future as well as in the present. <br><strike>\ndsfsdfsdfsdf</strike><br>\nFirstly, friends who grew in the varied environment have definitely different opinion even in the same subject. When people communicate with them, they can broaden their view of the world and improve abilities of understanding other people. For example, in the High School, I have friends whom other classmates called them strange. In this time, I could really get and build broad mind because they make me like that. <br>\n<br>\nOn top of that, different friends help people to be able to adapt to society in the present and even in the  future. They are different in ways to meet and manage varying situations. When people watch them and are affected by the ways they receive the situations, they can develop their own way which they couldn’t take alone. For instance, after graduating High School when I grew with the friend I mentioned above, I really adapted well to University even if there are a lot of unkind and ungenerous people. I think it is due to my high-school friends’ lives. <br>\n<br>\nTo sum up, in the environment with different types of friends, people broaden their opinion of the world and can develop ability to live in the society without the bigger problem. In this regard, I disagree with the statement that it is better to have friends who are lots of afimities than those who are different."', '', '', '', 0, 0, 'essay', 'Tagging', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2013-11-26 03:04:42');
INSERT INTO `tag_essay` VALUES(183, 14, 59, 0, '\n" Some people believe that success in life comes from taking risks or chances. Others believe that success results from careful planning. In your opinion, what does success come from? Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer."', '"Everyone has the urge to succeed in life. That is why we try to work hard and set our goals. Success in ones'' life may come from many different reasons. In my opinion, being passionate about what you do is essential to be successful in life. The reasoning behind this is that people with passion don''t give up easily and they have their own goal.\n To begin with, people with passion are energized enough to keep going even after few failures. There are only few people can succeed in one try and eveybody wants to be that few people. But in life, some failures are inevitable and some people might just quit after few trys. Nevertheless, passionate people can learn from their mistakes and failures and they always make progress on their work. To illustate this point, there was a many men like Bill Gates who wanted to make a computer affordable to common households. At the end, there was only him left because it was he who had the most passion and never gived up even after some failures. Being passionate about something can help people to become successful.\n On top of that, passionate people have their own goals. Success is the achievement of goals. People who are enthusiatic about their work set their goal and never give up. Some goals might seem ridiculous to others but they pursue them anyway. To give a personal example, when my grandmother first started to study psychology at the community center, everyone didn''t understanded her because she was in her 60''s. Even my parents thought it was too later for her to study new things. For my grandmother, what other people said didn''t mattered to her. She kept on studying and got her license in two years. Now, she is working at a community center as a part-time teacher. Her passion toward study was admirable and that is what made her push hard to achieve her goal.\n To summarize, I firmly believe that success is gained by passion. This is because people with never give up and aim for their goals. This is what makes successful people different from the rest of us.\n\n"', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 'essay', 'Tagging', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
INSERT INTO `tag_essay` VALUES(184, 14, 60, 0, '\nOne can easily get a lot of information about a person via the books and movies they like.', '"As the mass media is bigger than ever before, many people can find out the information about celebrities via books and movies. some people often think they could know the information about their famous athletes or movie actors easily through these things. However, in my opinion, we cannot easily get a lot of information about a person through the books and movies for two reasons: people do not know whether the information they''ve got is real or not, and it is too limited to find the information from the books and movies.\n\nTo begin with, it is hard for us to recognize that the information is really true. this is because many famous actors, entertainers and athletes used to disguise them for public. they always want to show the advantageous aspects of them and hide their disadvantages. In this way, celebrities can make people see them as the person they want to be seen like. For example, korean people were so surprised that many famous korean entertainers are accused of habitual taking drugs. People always thought these celebrities are so kind and honest because movies and books make these celebrities to be seen like the man the public cannot imagine to do that. This implies that the information from the books and movies cannot be the tool for judging others accurately.\n\nOn top of that, it is too narrow range to find the information through the books and movies. This is due to the fact that people cannot put all of information into these books and movies and cannot easily find the information they want compared to the internet. We all know that now we are living in the information-age. we can easily find the vast data of information about a person through the one-click button on the internet. however, people cannot easily find out the information through the books and movies because these contain limited data. Suppose that we want to find the scandal issue of Mr. Jackson. If we try to get the information from the books and movies, we will have a terrible time to find such a thing. Contrarily, we can get more easily if we use the internet.\n\nTo sum up, finding information about a person via the books and movies is not a good idea because they are untrustworthy and limited. In this regard, people should  know the aspects of the truth of a person through other materials, not by movies or books. "', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 'essay', 'Tagging', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
INSERT INTO `tag_essay` VALUES(185, 14, 61, 0, '\nWhich of the following do you prefer? Having a job that pays a low salary but is secure or a job that pays a high salary but is easy to lose', '"It is evident that in our society, having a job is fairly important. Some people say that having a job that\npays a high salary but is easy to lose is better than having a job that pays a low salary but it is secure. However, I disagree with those people because of the following 2 reasons which are efficiency and\nless stress.\n \nFirst of all, having a job that pays a low salary but is secure is efficient. This is because it allows\npeople not to waste their money. Take my friend Tom for example. He normally spends a lot of money\nto buy clothes so he always suffered from lack of money. However, his attitude towards spending\nmoney changed a lot when he got a job that pays him low salary but is secure. He realized the importance of money and started not to waste them. Now he use his money wisely and never regrets after he\nuse them. On the other hand, his best friend Jack was a man who never spend money to buy\nunnecessary things before he was hired by a company which offers him high salary but is not secure.\nHigh salary made he''s friends to call him every weekend to buy meals for them. Eventually, he spent all of his monthly payment only after two weeks from the date he recieved his money. What is worse\nwas the company he was hired from went out of business due to lack of budget. So he lost all of his \nfriends, his girl friend stood him up and his family turned their back against him. As experience of Tom\nand his friend Jack shows, low paying job but secure is more efficient than high paying jobs that are\nunsecure.\n                        \nOn top of that, low paying secure job allows people to have less stress. This is because the job can \nassure people that they are earning money. This reminds me of a time when I had a part time job. I got a high salary but unfortunately, is was unsecure. This gave a lot of stress because I had to pay the tuition fee all by myself and it gave me a thinking that I would not be able to continue my studies due to\nuncertainty of my paying day. I was so stressed out that I suffered from stomach ulcer and had to be\nhospitalized for two months. As my experience shows, high paying jobs but unsecure have a drawback thus it is not a good choice for people.\n \nIn a nutshell, if I have given a choice to choose between a low paying job but is secure and a high paying job but is unsecure, I will definately choose the former one because it is more efficient for me and\ngives me less stress than the later one."', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 'essay', 'Tagging', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
INSERT INTO `tag_essay` VALUES(186, 14, 62, 0, '\nDo you agree or disagree with the following statement? Television has destroyed communication among friends and family. Use specific reasons and examples to support your opinion.', '"In this argument, some people maintain that television has destroyed communication among family and friends. To support the argument, the people may cite the fact that many research has shown the result that the number of communication has significantly dropped among most of families recently. However, I firmly disagree with the argument with several reasons. In other words, the argument is problematic for the following reasons; the decreased number of communications within family and friends is caused by other factors. Moreover, recent media, such as Television or radio, can stimulate interaction among people.\n \nSome people assume that television has disturbed interaction within family or friends. However, this argument provides no evidence to support the assumption. In fact, this is not necessarily the case. For example, this is possibility that the lacks of communication are caused by other factors. In other words, this argument is vulnerable to the criticism that, if most of people who are not interacting with other people frequently has interested in debating or discussing through the internet after development of online communities, the argument cannot be valid in any sense. Moreover, Television can motivate communication among people. For example, In a recent survey, conducted by the Harvard Business Review in 2011, comparing to people who do not watch television at all, people who watch some dramas or news on television have a tendency to discuss with colleagues and family members. In other words, television can provide some sources to discuss for people who want to talk with other people.\n \nAll things considered, because the argument that television has destroyed communication among family and friends leaves out several key issues; it is not completely sound or persuasive. To strengthen the conclusion of the argument, the author should include above mentioned assumptions and provide evidences to support these assumptions. Moreover, a recent survey has shown that television does not disturb communication but stimulate talks among people. Therefore, I think that, if people can properly use several topics and issues broadcasted by television, this media can be definitely helpful for people to communicate each other."', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 'essay', 'Tagging', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
INSERT INTO `tag_essay` VALUES(187, 14, 63, 0, '\nIt is better to learn about foreign countries from newspapers and magazines than to visit those countries.', '"Some people think that learning about foreign countries from diversity articles is more beneficial from visiting those worlds. There is a lot of truth in it. However, in my opinion, it is more advantages for people to visit a lot of manifold cities than reading societies through books for two reasons; practical assistance and valuable life lessons.\n To begin with, traveling other countries allows people to have practical assistance. Going abroad is possible for them to get a lot of helpful experience, it also enables people these days to have accumulated their own know-how in their careers or lives. Thus, they have many resources and skills with which to teach and guide non-experienced people. For example, I learned much more from my senior employees than from my peers when I first started working at a tour company. Because my peers did not have much work experience, we were not able to learn much from each other. On the other hand, the senior employees in my department taught me many important work skills, such as how to create effective presentations and how to safely handle the machinery in the lab. They helped me greatly, and thanks to them, I was able to acclimate easily to the work place.\n On the top of that, older people who have a more traveling adventure teach younger people valuable life lessons. This is due to the fact that, younger people can learn valuable lessons from older people who are more mature and tend to have understanding of life. In this respect, older people’s understanding can affect younger people’s lives in positive ways. For instance, after failing multiple times to pass the exam to become an English teacher, my sister became extremely discouraged. Most of her friends advised her to pursue a different career, and she soon stressed about her professional future. Meanwhile, my parents advised her to continue studying and try to pass the examination again. To encourage her to stick with her goal, they told her stories of how they overcame failures in their own lives. Because of their advised, my sister rose to the challenge, passed her exam, and finally became a teacher last year.\n To sum up, it is more important knocking other foreign countries doors in person than meet in books their countries. This is because learning about foreign countries by use of visiting those can have positive impact on receive help from others and have a more comprehensive understanding of life. In this regard, I strongly disagree with the idea that reading countries on magazines for the reasons I mentioned above."', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 'essay', 'Tagging', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
