INSERT INTO `tag_essay` VALUES(192, 15, 56, 0, '\nThe most important period in a person’s life is one’s twenties. Use specific reasons and example to support your opinion', '" Some people believe that childhood is the most important time in person`s life, because during childhood, people establish their value systems, characters and relationships. However, I am convinced that twenties are the most important time of the life. That is because career is usually determined in twenties, and most people tend to get married in this period.\n \n To begin with, many people decide their future careers in this period. To be specific, people usually get first jobs in their twenties. University students start to work as full-time workers after they graduate, when they may be around 25, and this decision must be the most influential thing in their life, since lots of factors like future incomes, occupation satisfactions depend on their jobs. It is definitely essential components in life. For example, when I was 25, I had to choose whether I would work for Energy corportation or plant engineering. After contemplating, I decided to get into an energy company. That was a huge opportunity in my life. I am so satisfied with working envirnment and enough payment. On the other hand, Plant engineering suffers from serious recession these days. If I chose to work for plant engineering company, I might struggle to find another job.\n \n On top of that, lots of people get married in their twenties. In fact, marriage is the most important decision in our life. Husband or Wife is the one, their spouse spend majority of time together for the entire life. Moreover, after marriage, we broaden and establish our relationships, which will affect our life enoumously. For instance, before I got married, I always felt very lonely. However, since I got married, my wife always took care of me and tried to be with me. So I became very happy with my life. Moreover, I get to know lots of people, such as my wife`s friends and family. They have a positive effect on my life. Some of them gave me precious advice and I respect them as role-models as well.\n \n To sum up, In our twenties, our future careers are decided and many people get married. In this regard, I firmly believe that one`s twenties is the most important period in one`s life.      "', '" Some people believe that childhood is the most important time in person`s life, because during childhood, people establish their value systems, characters and relationships. However, I am convinced that twenties are the most important time of the life. That is because career is usually determined in twenties, and most people tend to get married in this period.<br><br>\n To begin with, many people decide their future careers in this period. To be specific, people usually get first jobs in their twenties. University students start to work as full-time workers after they graduate, when they may be around 25, and this decision must be the most influential thing in their life, since lots of factors like future incomes, occupation satisfactions depend on their jobs. It is definitely essential components in life. For example, when I was 25, I had to choose whether I would work for Energy corportation or plant engineering. After contemplating, I decided to get into an energy company. That was a huge opportunity in my life. I am so satisfied with working envirnment and enough payment. On the other hand, Plant engineering suffers from serious recession these days. If I chose to work for plant engineering company, I might struggle to find another job.<br>\n <br>\n On top of that, lots of people get married in their twenties. In fact, marriage is the most important decision in our life. Husband or Wife is the one, their spouse spend majority of time together for the entire life. Moreover, after marriage, we broaden and establish our relationships, which will affect our life enoumously. For instance, before I got married, I always felt